  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fiscal Justice for Women and Girls (FJWG) in Africa</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project goal is to contribute to more transparent and accountable revenue generation and spending policies by transforming fiscal systems to better respond to the needs of citizens, especially for women and girls in Zambia. It will draw on research from the Fair Tax Monitor methodology to demonstrate gaps in fiscal policies and to advance policy alternatives to increase domestic resources from a far tax system and highlight spending priority that lead to reduced gender inequalities. The project will build capacity of local NGOs and Women&apos;s Rights organisations (WROs) and mobilise communities to be actively involved in policy change and investment priorities by government at central and local levels.</narrative>
  </description>
